YoY Sales 12

1.     1.Right Click on Average price sheet and select Duplicate . Change the name of the sheet to YOY Sales. Remove avg Prices from the marks shelf by dragging to the left side.




      2. Drag and drop to the following to Text under Marks

      a. YOY sales

      b.  cc. Mark Sales KPI Indicator Down

       c. cc. Mark Sales KPI Indicator UP



3. Right click on YOY sales under marks shelf and select format > Pane > Numbers Custom > Percentage > Decimal places 2





4. Click on Text select the ellipses (…) and Highlight all the text select Tableau Bold. Select Font size 12 and Font type Bold. Click on the Alignment and select Horizontal Center and Vertical Center




5. Select <AGG(YoY)> click on the color and select Brown color (#9d7660) Likewise select <AGG(cc. Mark Sales KPI Indicator UP)> and change the color to Green (#59a14f)

<AGG(cc. Mark Sales KPI Indicator Down)> and change the color to Red (#e15759). Arrange in one line Click Click Ok.









6. Rt click on title and erase everything and enter YoY Sales> font type Tableau Semi bold > Font size 10 > Bold > Align center.
